quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Confirm Box[/h1]

A [b]confirm box[/b] is often used to have the user verify or accept something.
When a confirm box pops up, the user must click either OK or Cancel to proceed.
If the user clicks OK, the box returns [b]true[/b]. If the user clicks Cancel, the box returns [b]false[/b].

[b]Example:[/b] [code format="js" codeId="685"]var result = [b]confirm[/b]("Do you really want to leave this page?");
if (result == true) {
  alert("Thanks for visiting");
}
else {
  alert("Thanks for staying with us");
}[/code]
[b]Result:[/b]  [img id="2991" width="100%"] 
The result when the user clicks [b]OK[/b]: [img id="2763" width="100%"]
The result when the user clicks [b]Cancel[/b]: [img id="2764" width="100%"]
